132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 399
H.P. 253 House of Representatives, February 4, 2025
An Act to Amend the Laws Regarding the Retention of Proceeds
from Municipal Foreclosures
Reference to the Committee on Taxation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MCINTYRE of Lowell.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 36 MRSA ยง943-C, sub-ยง10, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 640, ยง3, is amended
3 to read:
4 10. Transfer Retention of proceeds. If, after provision of notice under subsection 9,
5 a former owner fails to claim the excess sale proceeds within 30 days of the final published
6 notice, the municipality shall transfer retain the excess sale proceeds to the Unclaimed
7 Property Fund under Title 33, section 2141.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill provides that if the former owner of property that was foreclosed upon by a
1100 municipality, after notification by that municipality, fails to claim the excess sale proceeds
1111 within 30 days of the final published notice, the municipality must retain the excess sale
1122 proceeds. Current law requires the municipality to transfer the excess sale proceeds to the
1133 Unclaimed Property Fund.
